chunks.text: ## MAXIMO SELF-PACED TRAINING GUIDE ## HEALTHCARE TECHNOLOGY MANAGEMENT - HTM TECH TRAINING ## HTM Tech Roles in Maximo In Maximo, HTM Techs/Tech Plus roles can review and create related Work Orders to Service Requests, review, assign, take ownership, update statuses and complete Work Orders. The difference between the HTM Tech and HTM Tech Plus role is that the Tech cannot assign Work Orders to another Tech whereas the Tech Plus can. ## Available Training Resources User Guides, Job Aids and Quick Reference Documents are available on the EAWM Maximo Training Page to help users learn their role and responsibilities in Maximo at their own pace and in a mode that best fits their learning style. - · User Guides provide the greatest amount of detail on each topic. User Guides include a high-level summary, detailed step-by-step instructions with screen captures, and a Business Process Model mapping out the activities performed by each affected Functional Community.

r Guides include a high-level summary, detailed step-by-step instructions with screen captures, and a Business Process Model mapping out the activities performed by each affected Functional Community. User Guides can be found in the 'Training Materials by Role' section of the Training page, under via links to the Functional Community and Role name. - · Job Aids target critical functionality in Maximo. These documents are intended to be brief and focus on key issues, highlighting essential steps. These are found in the 'User Documentation' section of the Training page. - · Quick Reference Documents (QRDs) include step-by-step work instructions, in simplest terms. Unlike Job Aids and User Guides, QRDs normally do not include screen captures. These are also posted in the 'User Documentation' section. In addition to the items available on the Training page, this Self-Paced Training Guide directs you to short video demonstrations recorded and narrated by Maximo Instructors as they walk through the steps of completing specific tasks in Maximo. To train for your role, read the appropriate User Guide, Job Aid and/or QRD for a given topic to gain an understanding of the process. Also, watch the video demonstrations as noted below. Continue reviewing this information until you are ready to start working in Maximo. IMPORTANT! Please DO NOT attempt to practice any of the steps in the Maximo Production system. If, after reviewing the materials, you are still uncomfortable with working in Maximo, contact your Maximo Site Lead for additional guidance. ## MAXIMO SELF-PACED TRAINING GUIDE ## 1. Request Work HTM Techs can use the Maximo Service Requests application to create a new Service Request and the Work Order Tracking application to create new Work Orders.

Request Work HTM Techs can use the Maximo Service Requests application to create a new Service Request and the Work Order Tracking application to create new Work Orders. In some cases, only the Work Order will be created. Service Requests are used to request work to be done by another Department. - · To read the User Guide on this topic, please go to the HTM Tech Training Materials page; under the HTM Tech tab, select the Request Work User Guide to download the file. - · To see demonstrations of using Maximo, please go to the EAWM Maximo Video Demos. Under the section, Healthcare Technology Management (HTM) , locate the videos for the role HTM Tech/Plus . The following video demonstrations pertain to this topic (please note that the videos will launch in a separate media player): - o Create a Service Request - o Create Related Work Order from Service Request - o Create a New Work Order without a Service Request - o Print Work Order ## 2.

Asset Turn In Work Order Completing an Asset Turn In Work Order is the same as completing any Work Order in Maximo. The key difference is to ensure Sanitization and/or Decontamination of the Asset(s) is completed by the Responsible Tech and depending on your local business process, verified by a Supervisor. If authorized, a Tech can verify sanitization. Key points to remember are that once work is completed, the Work Order must be in the Status of COMPLETE and the associated Service Request in the Status of WSAN (Waiting on Sanitization).
